            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "This school is one of the most suitable options for students who want to have fun in their life\nAcademics wise this school is one of THE MOST PARTIAL and careless school. There is this award called all- rounder which is given to 3 people from a class and it is given to the people who deserve it the least.  If the class teacher likes you, you get it. Im not joking. I got 97 percent in boards, participated and won in many olympiads, participated in many sports events and extra curricular activities, had a good attendance record, but I've never received the award even once. I'm not saying this out of hate or anger, but just worry and sadness. I've worked hard all through my grade and tried my best, and pass with extremely good marks, but only the people who are the favorites of teachers are the ones who are rewarded even if they do not do academically good\nAlso teachers judge students so much, and assume your capability and have vengeance on students\nOne of the worst experiences in the School\nBut otherwise the students, the Cultural all those stuff are real good",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
