            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "My son is studying in third std at psbb gerugambakkam. They announced a change in school uniform and asked us to purchase it from Ramachandra silks at porur merely 5 days before reopening!!!! We went today, that place was worse than the busiest market!! The sales people at the shope were so rude and were screaming at the parents if we asked for a different size or any other doubt. \" If you want, you find out for yourself, I don't have the time. This is the only size available now, if you want you buy\". Why should we parents go through this kind of a humiliation??? If the school wants to change their, they should have done it at their own campus atleast a month prior. They know the strength of each class, why couldn't they do it in an orderly fashion???? We pay such humongous amount as fees to go through such offensive comments?? The clothes are also of cheap quality and it was overly priced.. because of lack of parking, we even got a parking ticket!! at the end of the day a place of wisdom has become a place of business!!!",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
